underwent transplantation after achieving a partial response (PR) and 4 patients 
were non-responders.
RESULTS: Following HDC/ASCT, 23 (66%) of the patients achieved a CR, 4 (11%) a 
PR and in 7 (20%) cases the transplant failed. One patient was not evaluated 
because of early toxic death. With a median follow-up of the survivors of 37.5 
months, 18 patients (51%) are alive and 15 patients (43%) are free of disease. 
Transplant-related mortality rate at 100 days was 11% and at 5 years the 
